Israelâ€™s  TA-25 index  declined to its
lowest intraday level since May 24, sliding 0.7 percent to
1,049.12 at 11:24 a.m. in  Tel Aviv . The gauge has dropped 9.9
percent this month.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Allot Communications Ltd. (ALLT)   headed for the highest
close on record, advancing 7.9 percent to 101.3 shekels, or the
equivalent of $26.12. The U.S.-traded stock of the Israeli maker
of high-speed networking equipment added 11 percent to $26.40 in
 New York  yesterday.  Israel Corp. (ILCO)   headed for the biggest drop in a
week, retreating 1.7 percent to 2,134 shekels. The holding
company with investments in shipping, chemicals and
construction, said its loss widened to $82 million from $57
million in the same period last year.  Migdal Insurance & Financial Holding Ltd. (MGDL)  
declined 1.8 percent to 5.111 shekels, the lowest intraday level
since May 22. The insurance holding company said first-quarter
net income declined 20 percent to 90.7 million shekels ($23.4
million) from 112.9 million shekels in the same period a year
earlier.  Jerusalem Economy Ltd. (ECJM)   declined 2.5 percent, the
most since May 24 in intraday trading, to 23.40 shekels. The
operator of office, industrial and commercial buildings, posted
a loss of 37.6 million shekels in the first quarter after a
profit of 167 million shekels a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
